TERA — Spatial-Temporal Axis Model

Abstract

TERA models dynamic systems using a minimal geometric framework that combines spatial dimensions with temporal dimensions to form a stable logical body. The system operates through the interaction of information, energy and time, allowing states to evolve through structured decision gates.

The model is designed as a meta-logic framework for simulations, autonomous systems, and complex system analysis.


---

1. Fundamental Axes

Classical physics describes a system using three spatial dimensions and one temporal dimension.

TERA expands this idea by separating time into two functional components.

The system therefore operates on five axes.

3 Spatial Axes
2 Temporal Axes

Which gives:

X, Y, Z
τ (local time)
ω (temporal frequency)


